The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | China calls for nuke balance
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     China calls for nuke balance
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	New Delhi, Sept. 2: China today asked the Nuclear Suppliers Group to strike a balance between non-proliferation and peaceful uses of atomic energy.        
	Foreign ministry spokesperson Jiang Yus comment came ahead of talks in Vienna on September 4-5 when the atomic cartel takes up Americas proposal to exempt India from the groups strict trade regulations.        
	PTI also quoted her as saying that China had always played a positive role at NSG meets and Indian officials said they hoped Beijing wouldnt come in the way of the waiver.        
	China also said it was committed to developing a strategic partnership with India. Both countries announced the visit of Chinese foreign minister Yang Jiechi to India from Sunday. Yang is scheduled to formally open the Chinese consulate in Calcutta.                                                                                                                                                                         
